org.openimaj.math.geometry.shape.algorithm

Class ProcrustesAnalysis

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openimaj.math.geometry.shape.algorithm.ProcrustesAnalysis

  • public class ProcrustesAnalysis
extends Object
    Ordinary Procrustes Analysis between two sets of corresponding PointLists. It is assumed that the number of points in the PointLists is equal, and that their is a one-to-one correspondance between the ith point in each list.
    Author:
    Jonathon Hare (jsh2@ecs.soton.ac.uk)

      • ProcrustesAnalysis

        public ProcrustesAnalysis(PointList reference,
                  boolean normalise)
        Construct the ProcrustesAnalysis with the given reference shape. The reference shape is optionally normalised to a standardised scale and translated to the origin.
        Parameters:
        reference - The reference shape.
        normalise - if true, then the reference is normalised (changing the reference shape itself).

      • align

        public Jama.Matrix align(PointList toAlign)
        Align the given shape to the reference. The alignment happens inplace, so the input points are modified. The matrix used to transform the points is returned.
        Parameters:
        toAlign - transform matrix
        Returns:
        aligned points (reference to toAlign)
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the input is null or has a different size to the reference.

      • computeProcrustesDistance

        public static float computeProcrustesDistance(PointList l1,
                              PointList l2)
        Compute the Procrustes Distance between two PointLists. If the distance is 0, then the shapes overlap exactly.
        Parameters:
        l1 - first shape
        l2 - second shape
        Returns:
        the calculated distance.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the input is null or has a different size to the reference.
